===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|univers}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|universum||all things, as a whole, the universe}}, neuter of {{term|universus||all together, whole, entire, collective, general, literally turned or combined into one}}, from {{term|uni-}}, combining form of {{term|unus||one}} + {{term|versus||turned}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|vertere||to turn}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈjuːnɪˌvɜːs/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈjunəˌvɝs/}}
* {{audio|en-us-universe.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɜː(r)s}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The sum of everything that exists in the cosmos, including time and space itself; same as the [[Universe]].
# An entity similar to our [[Universe]]; one component of a larger [[entity]] known as the [[multiverse]].
# Everything under consideration.
#: ''In all this '''universe''' of possibilities, there is only one feasible option.''
# An imaginary collection of worlds.
#: ''The '''universe''' in this comic book series is richly imagined.''
# Intense form of [[world]] in the sense of perspective or social setting.
#: ''That didn’t just rock my world, it rocked my '''universe'''.''

